title.narrative: Protection and resilience of women and girls in crisis response and recovery efforts including 'Covid19' are enhanced

description.narrative: This outcome will focus on strengthening the capacity of the humanitarian practitioners working in disaster and crisis response to undertake need assessments in a manner responsive to gender, age and disability status. It aims to enhance the capacity of the humanitarian community including practitioners and officials to design, plan and implement gender, age and disability responsive humanitarian action. More specifically, this outcome focuses on providing safe shelter and necessary life-saving information to crisis affected women and girls, especially meeting the emergency needs for the most vulnerable women and girls (e.g. elderly, pregnant and lactating mothers, disabled, gender diverse, engaged in vulnerable work, traumatized, lonely mothers, and abandoned/ unattended/ orphaned girls), while ensuring that they are actively engaged in the humanitarian operation.
